vars: {
  d2-config: {
    theme-id: 4
    layout-engine: elk
  }
}

title: |md
  # Epoll Edge-Triggered Algorithm
  Handling EPOLLIN on edge-triggered epoll
|

direction: right

classes: {
  step_box: {
    shape: rectangle
    width: 180
    height: 120
    style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
    style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
    style.stroke-width: 2
  }
  state_box: {
    shape: rectangle
    width: 280
    style.fill: "#FFF9E6"
    style.stroke: "#F4A259"
    style.stroke-width: 1
  }
  highlight: {
    style.fill: "#FFE0F5"
    style.stroke: "#E91E63"
    style.stroke-width: 2
  }
  changed: {
    style.bold: true
    style.font-color: "#E91E63"
  }
  arrow_conn: {
    style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
    style.stroke-width: 2
  }
}

Before_State: "BEFORE: epoll_wait returned" {
  shape: sql_table
  style.fill: white
  Socket_Buffer: "read buffer: [a,b,c,d,e,f,g]" {
    style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  }
  Buffer_Pointer: "read_offset: 0" {
    style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  }
  Socket_State: "EPOLLIN triggered" {
    style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  }
  Event_Count: "ready_events: 1" {
    style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  }
}

After_State: "AFTER: socket drained" {
  shape: sql_table
  style.fill: white
  Socket_Buffer_After: "read buffer: []" {
    style.fill: "#FFE0F5"
  }
  Buffer_Pointer_After: "read_offset: 7" {
    style.fill: "#FFE0F5"
  }
  Parsed_Commands: "7 bytes parsed" {
    style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  }
}

Before_State -> After_State: "Process EPOLLIN" {
  style.stroke: "#E91E63"
  style.stroke-width: 3
  style.stroke-dash: 0
  source-arrowhead.label: "step 1"
  target-arrowhead.label: "step 7"
}

Step_1: |md
  **Step 1: epoll_wait Returns**
  
  - Kernel signals EPOLLIN ready
  - Edge-triggered: must handle ALL available data
  - Don't wait for next iteration
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  width: 200
  height: 100
}

Step_2: |md
  **Step 2: recv() into Buffer**
  
  - Read from socket into read_buffer
  - May get partial data or multiple commands
  - Handle EAGAIN when buffer empty
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  width: 200
  height: 100
}

Step_3: |md
  **Step 3: Parse Complete Commands**
  
  - Check if buffer has complete RESP frame
  - resp_parse_partial() returns:
    - PARSE_INCOMPLETE (need more data)
    - PARSE_COMPLETE (got command)
    - PARSE_ERROR (malformed)
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  width: 200
  height: 100
}

Step_4: |md
  **Step 4: Execute Command**
  
  - If complete command parsed
  - Call command_process()
  - Then continue parsing (loop!)
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  width: 200
  height: 100
}

Step_5: |md
  **Step 5: Check for More Data**
  
  - Loop: try recv() again!
  - Edge-triggered: only notified ONCE
  - Must drain entire buffer before next epoll_wait
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  width: 200
  height: 100
}

Step_6: |md
  **Step 6: Handle EAGAIN**
  
  - recv() returns -1, errno=EAGAIN
  - Socket buffer is EMPTY
  - Can now re-arm for next epoll_wait
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  width: 200
  height: 100
}

Step_7: |md
  **Step 7: Re-arm (Edge-Triggered)**
  
  - If buffer empty, mod_fd EPOLLIN
  - Next data will trigger new event
  - All 7 bytes parsed successfully!
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#E8F4FD"
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  width: 200
  height: 100
}

Step_1 -> Step_2: "1" {
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  source-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  target-arrowhead.shape: triangle
}

Step_2 -> Step_3: "2" {
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  source-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  target-arrowhead.shape: triangle
}

Step_3 -> Step_4: "3" {
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  source-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  target-arrowhead.shape: triangle
}

Step_4 -> Step_5: "4" {
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  source-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  target-arrowhead.shape: triangle
}

Step_5 -> Step_6: "5a" {
  style.stroke: "#E91E63"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  source-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  target-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  label: "more data?"
}

Step_5 -> Step_2: "5b" {
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  source-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  target-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  label: "yes"
}

Step_6 -> Step_7: "6" {
  style.stroke: "#2E86AB"
  style.stroke-width: 2
  source-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  target-arrowhead.shape: triangle
}

Step_7 -> Step_1: "back to wait" {
  style.stroke-dash: 3
  style.stroke: "#888888"
  source-arrowhead.shape: triangle
  target-arrowhead.shape: triangle
}

notes: |md
  **Key Points:**
  
  1. Edge-triggered: get ONE notification per ready state
  2. Must drain entire buffer before returning to epoll_wait
  3. Loop continues parsing until EAGAIN (buffer empty)
  4. If only handle one command and return, next data is LOST
  5. This is why the while(1) loop in handle_client_io() is critical
|